Jun 24 2003	Can't Beat It...	I stayed at the Ohio House back in the '80's' and it was around $50/night so when I wanted to go 6/03 I was afraid of what the pricing would be. I paid $89/night for a busy Chicago weekend...the hotels DIRECTLY across the street and down the block were asking $125+/night. All I did was watch an hour of TV and crashed...took a shower the next morning and left. I can't see paying for a lap of luxury in the hotel when there are so many places and things to do up there! The rooms are clean and unlike Motel 6 you get your choice of shower or bath!I am going to stay at Ohio House anytime I go for more than a one day stay.	
