Nov 11 2002	Decent place for a decent price	I've stayed in the Ohio House a few times over the past few years. It's a decent place for a decent price, with free parking. It's pretty clean, and while the furniture isn't brand new, it's really close to all the good spots, and it's on the &quot;good&quot; side of them all. It's a little noisy at night, but HEY - IT'S DOWNTOWN. The blocks on the far side of the motel from Michigan Ave seem a bit dicey, but there's really no reason to go there at night, anyway. I didn't see any hookers there, but to be honest, I wasn't looking, either. If you want the Hilton, then stay at the Hilton. Just get ready to pay $140 or more a night, plus $30 for parking daily. If you want a decent price with a great location, this is a relatively good place. It also has a very convenient little b-fast place that has good (though not too health conscious) food. Enough bang for your buck for my weekend, anyway.	
